courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
courses.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisiteDetails.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Computers in Society
courses.description: Introduction to the social, legal, and ethical issues of computing, including the professional code of ethics. Topics include how computer use affects society, communities, individuals, and work, at both local and global scales, in the contexts of risk, privacy, computer crime, intellectual property, and professional decision-making, taking into account legal, ethical, diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility principles to inform development of inclusive and accessible computing solutions that address the needs of diverse user communities. Students analyze scenarios that allow them to view ethical decision-making as a crucial part of understanding the world, computing, and their diverse interplay. Oral presentation and written reports are required.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisiteDetails.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.name: Exploration in Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.name: Basic Concepts of Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
courses.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Foundations of Computer Science
courses.description: Formal logic and its applications. Proof of correctness. Sets and combinatorics. Induction, recursion, and recurrence equations. Relations, functions, and graphs: shortest path and minimal spanning tree, planarity, Eulerian paths, Hamiltonian cycles. Algebraic structures, finite-state machines, turing machines, and computational notions.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Computer Organization and Assembly Language Programming
courses.description: Overview of computer organization. MIPS architecture, assembly and machine language, data representation, assembly and linking process, C programming and interfacing with assembly code.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisiteDetails.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.name: Exploration in Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.name: Basic Concepts of Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Computer Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description: Number systems, Boolean algebra, Karnaugh maps, logic gates, combinational circuit design, adders, multiplexers, flip-flops, counters, shift registers. Laboratory: Experiments with TTL logic gates, flip-flops and counters.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Programming in .NET/C#
courses.description: C# syntax and semantics with emphasis on object oriented programming, threads, I/O, collections, use of Visual Studio. Creation of GUI applications, network applications, database connectivity and web applications.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Junior Project
courses.description: Software development project requiring aspects of algorithms, data structures, programming, and software design.
courses.restrictions: Completion of 60 credit hours and permission of instructor required.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Computer Communication and Networks
courses.description: Network layers, Internet protocol stack, network architectures, and network security concepts. Network programming interfaces, including sockets.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisiteDetails.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Computer Organization and Assembly Language Programming
prerequisiteDetails.description: Overview of computer organization. MIPS architecture, assembly and machine language, data representation, assembly and linking process, C programming and interfacing with assembly code.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.name: Exploration in Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.name: Basic Concepts of Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Machine Learning
courses.description: Problem formulation and feature engineering. Supervised and unsupervised learning tasks and their implementation and performance assessment. Challenges with model training, memory allocation, parameter search, and fine-tuning.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
prerequisiteDetails.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

prerequisites.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisites.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Senior Project
courses.description: Major software development project requiring integration and application of knowledge and skills acquired in algorithms, data structures, programming, and software design.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
prerequisiteDetails.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

prerequisites.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisites.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Foundations of Computer Science
prerequisiteDetails.description: Formal logic and its applications. Proof of correctness. Sets and combinatorics. Induction, recursion, and recurrence equations. Relations, functions, and graphs: shortest path and minimal spanning tree, planarity, Eulerian paths, Hamiltonian cycles. Algebraic structures, finite-state machines, turing machines, and computational notions.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Special Projects
courses.description: Allows students to develop an understanding and working knowledge of a project-based learning environment. Software tools and time/team managements skills are utilized as well.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
prerequisiteDetails.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

prerequisites.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisites.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

prerequisites.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Computer Organization and Assembly Language Programming
prerequisiteDetails.description: Overview of computer organization. MIPS architecture, assembly and machine language, data representation, assembly and linking process, C programming and interfacing with assembly code.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.name: Exploration in Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.name: Basic Concepts of Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.

prerequisites.name: Computer Engineering
prerequisites.description: Number systems, Boolean algebra, Karnaugh maps, logic gates, combinational circuit design, adders, multiplexers, flip-flops, counters, shift registers. Laboratory: Experiments with TTL logic gates, flip-flops and counters.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Special Projects
courses.description: Allow students to develop an understanding and working knowledge of a project-based learning environment. Software tools and time/team management skills are utilized as well.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
prerequisiteDetails.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

prerequisites.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisites.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

prerequisites.name: Computer Engineering
prerequisites.description: Number systems, Boolean algebra, Karnaugh maps, logic gates, combinational circuit design, adders, multiplexers, flip-flops, counters, shift registers. Laboratory: Experiments with TTL logic gates, flip-flops and counters.

courses.subject: CMPS
courses.name: Special Topics in Computer Science
courses.description: Alternate subtitles will appear on student's transcript.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
prerequisiteDetails.description: Algorithm analysis and asymptotic notation. Advanced data structures analysis. Design and analysis of: divide-and-conquer algorithms, dynamic programming, greedy algorithms, and amortized analysis; multithreaded algorithms, linear programming, number-theoretic algorithms, computational geometry and approximation algorithms.

prerequisites.name: Advanced Data Structures and Software Engineering
prerequisites.description:
Programming methods, software testing, and algorithm analysis. Construction, traversal, and modification of trees, heaps, and has tables. Sorting and searching techniques on linear structures including arrays and sequential files. 

A student will be permitted to enroll in CMPS 260 and CMPS 261 a maximum of three times in each course.

prerequisites.name: Honors Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Accelerated coverage of CMPS 150 and CMPS 260. Students passing CMPS 250 with a "C" or better will also receive credit for CMPS 150.

prerequisiteDetails.name: Computer Organization and Assembly Language Programming
prerequisiteDetails.description: Overview of computer organization. MIPS architecture, assembly and machine language, data representation, assembly and linking process, C programming and interfacing with assembly code.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Data Structures and Software Design
prerequisites.description: Integrated software engineering principles, fundamental data structures, and algorithm design and development. Requirements, specifications, design, implementation and testing.

prerequisites.name: Exploration in Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Constructing and programming of a robot. Problem solving, structured design of and implementation of algorithms, testing and debugging of programs, data types, control structures and abstractions.

prerequisites.name: Basic Concepts of Computer Science and Robotics
prerequisites.description: Concepts of computing and the interaction of computers with the physical world. Construction and operation of a robot by integrating electronics, mathematics, physics and computer programming.

prerequisites.name: Introduction to Computer Science
prerequisites.description: Problem solving, structured design of algorithms, implementation of algorithms, and testing and debugging of programs. Data types, control structures, and abstractions. The laboratory component focuses on algorithm design and implementation.
